      "content": "If your data fundamentally rebels against the assumptions of linear regression, you should absolutely pivot to a different modeling approach. This often means exploring Generalized Linear Models (GLMs), which allow you to specify different error distributions suited to your data, like Poisson or Gamma regression. For instance, if your housing prices are heavily skewed positive, a Gamma GLM might be a much better fit than forcing linearity. Think of it as ditching the rigid blueprint for a more flexible structure.",
